rComments: She brings a lot of energy to class and you can tell she is very passionate about auditing. There are a lot of readings and notes so it can be hard at times to keep up with all of that, but I think professor majors is a very good teacher overall.

A lot of topics covered within the class so keep up! She assigns a lot of outside readings and articles. There are a lot of slides. The grading is a bit nit picky so watch your wording with questions. Overall the class was fair just a lot of topics covered and sometimes it can be hard knowing which one is the most relevant for the exams.
